
// Verifying the integrity of a stream using a public key involves reading the stream's content and checking its signature against a provided public key. The [crypto.verify] slot is used to ensure that the data read from the stream has not been altered and was signed by the corresponding private key. The [public-key] slot specifies the key used for verification.
